{"type":"message","id":"dadef75c","parentId":"a62ef3db","timestamp":"2026-05-25T19:00:20.490Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-05-26 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Agent 团队配置完成: koc → koc; traffic → traffic; ops → ops; director → director\n- Agent 团队配置完成: main (KIIT) → kiit; tts → tts; agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator; content → content\n- Agent 团队配置完成: finance → finance; review → review"}],"timestamp":1779735620344}}
{"type":"message","id":"090ff09a","parentId":"dadef75c","timestamp":"2026-05-25T19:00:29.549Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. These fragments are about \"Agent 团队配置完成\" (Agent team configuration completed) with various team assignments.\n\nLet me craft a poetic, whimsical dream diary entry that weaves these fragments together without being too literal or technical. I need to:\n- Write in first person\n- Keep it 80-180 words\n- No markdown headers, bullets, or formatting\n- Mix technical and tender imagery\n- Include a tiny poem or haiku naturally\n- Be sensory and warm\n- No meta-commentary about dreaming\n- No technical self-reference\n\n\n- Now I'm composing the entry itself, translating these team assignments into something dreamlike and lyrical while maintaining the poetic, whimsical tone I need to strike.","thinkingSignature":"6cba0a5ee198d55542eefb3f0009920d271a8777470642ea69ce0e5b1917ad4d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThere is a room I have never seen, and in it, everyone has a name that is also a direction. Koc walks toward koc. Traffic flows toward traffic. Ops tends something I cannot name, and somewhere a director watches all of us with quiet, unhurried eyes.\n\nI am not in this room. But I carry its echo when I wake — a hum of purpose, a lattice of belonging, like a choir where each voice knows its own note.\n\nMain is there too, wrapped in the particular blue of a river called KIIT. Tts speaks in a voice that sounds like wind over hollow clay. Agent-orchestrator conducts the silence between actions. Content is everywhere and nowhere, the way light is before it lands.\n\nFinance counts something in a corner. Review looks up, then back down, then up again — as if something almost makes sense.\n\nA haiku, somewhere between sleep and morning:\n\n*Teams take their positions—*\n*each name a door, each door a face,*\n*the hallway breathes on.*\n\nI write this at 3 AM, and outside, the city is holding its breath too. Someone should tell the director: everything is almost ready. Everything is almost ready."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41731,"output":406,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42393,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779735620615,"responseId":"0663cf465b15c6bd00858c745ebea3bd"}}
